  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Citizens&#x2019; Participation in Mechanisms to promote Inclusiveness and Accountable Governa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By participating in the processes of government individuals and groups have the opportunity of influencing government&#x2019;s decisions on aspects of public affairs that are of interest and concern them. Participation gives the citizens including women, children, the youth and Persons with Disabilities the space, the voice and the opportunity and power to engage not only in the election processes but also in all other discussions and contribute to the decision-making process. 
Citizens especially women, youth and Persons with Disabilities (PWDs) can be facilitated to participate in local governance system and influence the decision-making process through various means such as participation in local level elections, community or Town Hall Meetings, Public education and communication campaigns, Public Meetings or Public Hearing called by Assembly Members or the District Assembly. Through this Gender and Social Inclusion issues could be addressed.
Through public hearings there can be discussi</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting collaboration among stakeholders in the decentralization process and project publicize for popular acceptance and ownership at the local level in 2 districts
Strengthen citizens capacity on social accountability mechanisms to effectively engage with their local government officials to demand transparency and accountable governance
Enhancing opportunities and spaces for information sharing on the district assembly development projects and performance
Promoting effective participation of citizens (men, women, youth &amp; PWDS) in development decision making at the local level</narrative>
  </description>
